item.description: When I was growing up, I always knew my mom was the cool mom. In the early 80s she was into newwave music like Romeo Void and Classix Nouveaux. I had no idea about that music. But I listened and still listen to it to this day. And she had Neil Diamond and Elton John records that I would play all the time. I was exposed to so many things that helped shape me.
